  "text": "The list of predicted miRNA-39UTR interactions is always ranked according to the single hypothesis P value (P SH ), which is a statistical score capable to account simultaneously for single and multiple binding sites as well as to accommodate accessibility and/ or conservation filters. P SH is an approximate probability that a given oligomer (e.g., a 7-mer), complementary to the miRNA seed, is found by chance at least c times in the corresponding 39UTR. Lower values of P SH imply that the interaction is more likely to be functional (see Refs. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] for details about P SH ). P SH is computed as",
